      "waterfall": {
        "interestPriority": "On each payment date, available interest proceeds shall be applied in the following order of priority: (A) Payment of taxes and governmental fees owed by the Issuer and Issuer Profit Amounts; (B) Payment of Trustee Fees and Expenses (up to Senior Expenses Cap); (C) Payment of Administrative Expenses (up to Senior Expenses Cap less amounts paid in (B)); (D) Top-up of the Expense Reserve Account (at Collateral Manager's discretion); (E) Payment of the Senior Collateral Management Fee (0.15% p.a. on Collateral Principal Amount); (F) Payment of scheduled Hedge Payments, Hedge Termination Payments, and Hedge Replacement Payments; (G) Payment of interest on Class X Notes (including Class X Principal Amortisation Amount) and Class A Notes (EURIBOR + 1.47%); (H) Payment of interest on Class B-1 Notes (EURIBOR + 2.25%); (H-2) Payment of interest on Class B-2 Notes (fixed rate 5.50%); (I) If Class A/B Coverage Tests fail, redemption of notes per Note Payment Sequence; (J-K) Payment of current and deferred interest on Class C Notes (EURIBOR + 2.65%); (L) If Class C Coverage Tests fail, redemption of notes per Note Payment Sequence; (M-N) Payment of current and deferred interest on Class D Notes (EURIBOR + 4.00%); (O) If Class D Coverage Tests fail, redemption of notes per Note Payment Sequence; (P-Q) Payment of current and deferred interest on Class E Notes (EURIBOR + 6.84%); (R) If Class E Par Value Test fails, redemption of notes per Note Payment Sequence; (S-T) Payment of current and deferred interest on Class F Notes (EURIBOR + 8.31%); (U) If Class F Par Value Test fails (post-Reinvestment Period), redemption of notes per Note Payment Sequence; (V) If Reinvestment OC Test fails (during Reinvestment Period), diversion of up to 50% of remaining proceeds; (W) Payment of Subordinated Management Fee (0.25% p.a.) and repayment of Collateral Manager Advances; (X-Z) Payment of excess Trustee Fees, Administrative Expenses, and Defaulted Hedge Termination Payments; (AA) Transfer to Supplemental Reserve Account (at Collateral Manager's discretion); (BB) Payment of Incentive Collateral Management Fee (20.0% of residual above IRR threshold); (CC) Remainder to Subordinated Notes as residual distributions.",
        "postAcceleration": "Following an Event of Default and acceleration, all available proceeds (both interest and principal) shall be applied sequentially: first to pay Trustee and administrative fees, then to pay hedge counterparties, then to redeem each class of notes in order of seniority until paid in full, and finally to Subordinated Notes.",
        "principalPriority": "On each payment date, available principal proceeds shall be applied in the following order of priority: (A) Shortfall payments from Interest Priority of Payments (paragraphs A through H-2); (B-N) Coverage test cure payments on a sequential basis for each class; (O) Reinvestment OC Test cure payments; (P) Special Redemption Amounts (if applicable); (Q) During Reinvestment Period: reinvestment in additional collateral obligations; after Reinvestment Period: limited reinvestment from credit improved/credit risk sales and unscheduled principal; (R) After Reinvestment Period: sequential redemption of notes in order of seniority; (S) Payment of Subordinated Management Fee and other junior expenses; (T) Reinvestment Amounts to Reinvesting Noteholders; (U) Incentive Collateral Management Fee (20.0% of residual above IRR threshold); (V) Any remaining principal proceeds to Subordinated Notes."
      },
